(1223, 161, '2016-03-10 20:21:54', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p class="journal-inner"><span class="drop-cap">I</span> started working out at the age of 16. At that age you''re mostly thinking about the benefits that being in shape can bring; girls and respect. Except In my experience it was eternally boring. Which was ok because working out was about reaping the benefits. Still... pick up dumbbell, curl, repeat. Sit up, lay down, repeat.</p>\r\n<p class="journal-inner">Fast forward to adulthood, we had been thinking of ways to get into a workout regiment that would peak our interest. One day we had a meeting with a potential hire for DiRocco''s wholesale distribution next to a boxing gym. While we waited for his arrival we decided to take a peak upstairs. Now, anyone who has seen Rocky can attest to the romance of the boxing gym. The lack of pampering and air conditioning. Just raw training. We were hooked.</p>\r\n<p class="journal-inner">A couple of weeks passed and our good friend Luis (who also runs all of our I.T./web) told us about a boxing gym closer to home base. Luis is the anti-stereotype for I.T. he''s been in and out of boxing gyms, Muay Thai, MMA, boxing, throughout his life. Case in point, he''s a good guy to have next to you if you ever find yourself in a scuffle.</p>\r\n<p class="journal-inner">Boxing not only gives you the aesthetics you''re looking for, it helps you get better acquainted with your body. You know yourself better, your limitations and how to push them. You get the muscles and the definition but they come as a byproduct of what you''re really trying to achieve: being more in tune with yourself.</p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Pound for pound', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2016-03-10 20:21:54', '2016-03-10 20:21:54', '', 0, 'https://www.diroccoeyewear.com/?p=1223', 0, 'post', '', 0),
