ize: 1em; font-variant: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #2b2b2b; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0062765/?ref_=nm_flmg_act_11" target="_blank">Bullitt</a></em><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1em; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit;"> had made him a bona-fide star, the biggest in Hollywood. A global cinema and style icon, the “king of cool” could all but guarantee box-office returns, so when Cinema Center Films signed a six-picture deal with Mr McQueen’s company, Solar Productions, they must have thought they’d just been given a license to print money. They backed his first project,</span><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1em; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit;"> </span><em style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1em; font-variant: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Le Mans</em><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1em; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit;">, to the tune of $6m, at that time an astronomical figure (roughly $37.3m in today’s money), and brought in a raft of big-name Hollywood talents to help get it off the ground.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0em 0px 1.76471em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; line-height: 1.76471em; font-size: 1em; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit;">Sitting in the director’s chair was Mr John Sturges, the man who made Mr McQueen a star in</span><span style="font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit;"> </span><em style="font-family: inherit; font-variant: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; line-height: inherit; 